race.comment: MAKE A DECISION (2) has been knocking on the door in stronger company and is suited with the 2kg claim. Comes back 220m in trip with the blinkers applied for the first time. Maps well and finds the right race. RESTRICTED ACCESS (4) scored comfortably first-up but then disappointed over 1100m at Launceston after being in contention on the turn. Presents fitter and he can stick on a lot better back in class. ARAYA SUNSHINE (7) resumed at this level and needed the outing. She's placed 2/3 second-up and Pires is reunited. Has a soft gate and on song is good enough. Each way. GINGERSON (5) is a leader who brings two near misses, with the latest at the track this grade and trip. Keeps the handy 3kg claim and is sure to give a big sight.
